Genyris README

You need Java 1.4 JRE to run the Genyris interpreter. Check with your JRE
version with:

  $ java -version

Start the command-line interpreter with Java:

  $ java -jar genyris-bin.jar

You will see a message follwed by a prompt:

  *** Genyris is listening...

  >

Commands can be typed in, use two carriage returns
to terminate an indented statement.

Examples of Genyris code are in the
jar and can be loaded as follows:

     > load "/examples/queens.lin"

     ~ true ; Symbol

     > queen 8
     "
     "Q......."
     "....Q..."
     ".......Q"
     ".....Q.."
     "..Q....."
     "......Q."
     ".Q......"
     "...Q...."
     ""
     etc

More examples can be extracted with:

  $ jar -xf genyris-bin.jar

Look in the "examples" folder for files to peruse.

